  <!-- Section: Application Process -->
  <section id="application" class="scroll-mt-24 mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Application Process</h2>

    <p class="mb-4">
      Obtaining Swiss residence as a wealthy individual is a negotiated process, not a standardized application. You'll work closely with tax advisors and immigration lawyers.
    </p>

    <ComparisonTable columns={timelineColumns} rows={timelineRows} />

    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-8 mb-3">Step-by-Step Guide</h3>

    <div class="space-y-6">
      <div class="flex gap-4">
        <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-bold">1</div>
        <div>
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Engage Swiss Tax and Immigration Advisors</h4>
          <p class="text-neutral-600">This is not a DIY process. You need experienced Swiss advisors who know the cantonal authorities. They'll assess your situation, recommend cantons, and estimate likely tax amounts. Budget CHF 30,000-70,000 for professional fees.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="flex gap-4">
        <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-bold">2</div>
        <div>
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Select Canton and Negotiate Lump-Sum Tax</h4>
          <p class="text-neutral-600">Your advisor approaches cantonal tax authorities to negotiate terms. Factors include: your intended living expenses, property value, family size, and the canton's appetite for new forfait residents. This takes 2-6 months.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="flex gap-4">
        <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-bold">3</div>
        <div>
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Secure Accommodation</h4>
          <p class="text-neutral-600">You need a Swiss address to apply for residence. This typically means buying or renting property. For lump-sum residents, property is part of the living expenses calculation. Expect CHF 3-20M+ for purchase or CHF 5,000-20,000/month for luxury rentals.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="flex gap-4">
        <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-bold">4</div>
        <div>
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Submit Residence Permit Application</h4>
          <p class="text-neutral-600">Apply to the cantonal migration office (Migrationsamt) for Permit B. Provide: passport, proof of accommodation, proof of financial means, health insurance commitment, and the agreed tax arrangement. Non-EU citizens may face quotas.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="flex gap-4">
        <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-bold">5</div>
        <div>
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Receive Permit B and Register</h4>
          <p class="text-neutral-600">Once approved (2-8 weeks), you receive Permit B (temporary residence). Register at the local commune (Gemeinde). Obtain your Swiss ID card. You're now a Swiss resident with all associated rights and obligations.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="flex gap-4">
        <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-bold">6</div>
        <div>
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Enroll in Swiss Health Insurance</h4>
          <p class="text-neutral-600">Within 3 months, you MUST enroll in mandatory LAMal insurance. Choose an insurer, select your franchise (CHF 300-2,500), and add supplementary coverage as desired. Coverage is retroactive to arrival date.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="flex gap-4">
        <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-bold">7</div>
        <div>
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Long-Term: Permit C and Citizenship</h4>
          <p class="text-neutral-600">After 10 years (5 for some nationalities), apply for Permit C (permanent residence). Citizenship requires 10+ years residence, language proficiency (B1 in local language), and integration assessment. Lump-sum residents can naturalize but it's complex.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

